<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-30T21:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-30T21:48:00-05:00" n="922" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d922">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">330/11–3050: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United
                            Nations</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-30T21:48:00-05:00">November 30,
                                1950—9:48 p. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received November 30—10:14 p. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>917. Indian contacts with Chinese Communist Delegation. Re mytel 914 November
                        30. USGADel informed by Indian Delegation after close SC meeting today that
                        Sir B. N. Rau had definite appointment <pb facs="1296" n="1276" xml:id="pg_1276"/> call on General Wu of Chinese Communist Delegation
                        tomorrow at 11 a. m. Indian informant stated Rau did not intend make any
                        specific suggestions this occasion, but had primarily in mind ascertaining
                        what nature Wu’s thinking on present situation.</p>
                    <p>Department please repeat AmEmbassy New Delhi as <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 6.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>